<p>The <strong>Pre-Professional Conference (PPC) </strong>is an annual event held every Fall semester to give undergraduate students an opportunity to further explore post-graduate academic and career routes related to their respective fields of interest and study. It is sponsored by the College of Language and Letters, coordinated by faculty from the English Department, and organized by student academic society leaders from the participating academic departments. Now having run for over a decade, the PPC has each year become a bigger and better event on the BYU-Idaho academic calendar and has invited a range of esteemed guests, from accomplished writers and academics, to successful government and business leaders.</p>
<p>In addition to inviting guest speakers and panelists to the conference, students are also granted the opportunity to share their research or creative works in additional sessions of the PPC schedule. For those students interested in participating in the conference, please contact your respective department heads, and/or academic society leaders for more information. For information on upcoming or past conferences, please click the icons below:</p>
